+## Failed-read disclosure boundary
+
+ZenovFS1 no longer leaves disk bytes in the caller buffer after a sector or checksum failure. The copied prefix or complete candidate is zeroed before an error is returned. A kernel boot self-test deliberately corrupts one in-memory checksum, proves rejection and complete scrubbing, restores the checksum and proves the normal read still succeeds. This prevents a ring-3 caller from examining unverified bytes after a failed syscall.
+
